#string STR_PCH_SERIAL_IO_ACPI_MODE_HELP          #language en-US "I2C, SPI, UART devices will be exposed as PCI or ACPI devices. This option is not applicable to GPIO which is always ACPI device."
#string STR_PCH_SERIAL_IO_AUTO_LTR_MODE           #language en-US "Auto Mode"
#string STR_BT_MOVED                              #language en-US "BT device moved to Connectivity Configuration"
#string STR_PCH_SERIAL_IO_DEVICE_HELP             #language en-US "Enables/Disables SerialIo Controller\nIf given device is Function 0 PSF disabling is skipped. PSF default will remain and device PCI CFG Space will still be visible. This is needed to allow PCI enumerator access functions above 0 in a multifunction device.\nThe following devices depend on each other:\nI2C0 and I2C1,2,3\nUART0 and UART1,SPI0,1\nI2C4, I2C5 and UART2\nI3C0 and I3C2\n\n UART 0 (00:30:00) cannot be disabled when:\n1. Child device is enabled like CNVi Bluetooth (\_SB.PC00.UA00.BTH0)\n UART 0 (00:30:00) cannot be enabled when:\n1. I2S Audio codec is enabled (\_SB.PC00.I2C0.HDAC)"
#string STR_PCH_SERIAL_IO_I2C4_DEVICE_HELP        #language en-US "Enables/Disables SerialIo Controller\nFor I2C5 and UART2 to work this device has to be enabled"
#string STR_PCH_SERIAL_IO_I2C5_DEVICE_HELP        #language en-US "Enables/Disables SerialIo Controller\nFor this device to work I2C4 has to be enabled"
#string STR_PCH_SERIAL_IO_SPI2_DEVICE_HELP        #language en-US "Enables/Disables SerialIo SPI2 Controller\nThe following device depends from:\nThermal Subsystem in PCI mode\nOtherwise SPI2 will not appear in the OS"
#string STR_PCH_SERIAL_IO_SPI3_DEVICE_HELP        #language en-US "Enables/Disables SerialIo SPI3 Controller."
#string STR_PCH_SERIAL_IO_I2C3_I3C_DEVICE_HELP    #language en-US "Note: I3C cannot be enabled if I2C#3 is enabled due to an ITSS requirement that there are at most 4 unique IRQs per Device, whereas D21 has 5 functions"
#string STR_PCH_SERIAL_IO_HELP                    #language en-US "Control of the SerialIo device.\n\nDisabled = SerialIo will be unconditionally disabled\n\nEnabled = SerialIo will be Enabled if each SerialIo device in PCH is Disabled.\n"
#string STR_PCH_SERIAL_IO_I2C0                    #language en-US "I2C0 Controller"
